  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "### **Aptitude Practice Question**\n\nIf the length of a pole is 12m and the angle of elevation from the top of the pole to point If an angle on the ground is 45\u00b0, then find the distance of the pole from point A.<img alt=\"5\" height=\"287\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260618123433955817/5.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260618123433955817/5.webp 284w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260618123433955817/5-100.webp 99w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.o\n\n---\n\n### **Answer & Explanation**\n\nrg/wp-content/uploads/20260618123433955817/5-200.webp 198w\" width=\"284\"/> Pole height (opposite side) = 12 m\n\nAngle of elevation = 45\u00b0\n\ntan45\u00b0 \u200b= 12\u200b/CA\n\n1 = 12/CA\n\nCA= 12m\nTherefore, the distance of the pole from point A is 12m",
    "sampleTestCases": []
  }
}